76561198174165825,Not Recommended,252690,34629772,Posted: 31 August,all,Super Bad Boi,"I've been using Fantasy Grounds for about a year now. A lot of play time, but a solid 50 hours of that time is probably for porting 4e content so I could use it. While it is a product I use when I play D&D, it is also an annoyingly bad purchase that pisses me off when I have to ask others to get it to join my campaigns. I'm going to have a pro/con list that I believe sums up my problems with this ""game"", but I don't believe it is all of it since I will not purchase the dlc due to it's price and stupidity of the whole affair of this.Pros--o FG is most definitely the #1 option for accessibility and ease of understanding, it feels comfortable when you have played with it for about an hour.o The icons and token system feel good and allow map combat to benefit a lot since you can make icons connect to PC's and NPC's so that damage is calculated by the game and input onto sheets (as well as effects).o They give you some monsters and items for 5e to use without having to write them out yourself.o Rolling is easy and can be done by clicking or rolling directly on the chat window. It does the math and will specify damage type in the text window alongside the rolls.o The notes and story tabs are useful for longer-term games. I dig them and use them.Cons --o There is no map building feature and you have to obtain every image and token for youself unless you are willing to spend hard-earned dosh to get their images.o The game costs $30 more than it should for what it is, which is essentially a husk that asks you to paint it to make it look nice.o DLC... look at the prices and come back to me saying that is an okay thing to do with what they give you the the base kit. The acceptable ones are the modules, but some of the DLC just feels like money grubbing for the most basic scraps.o The system is old and that is certain from the boot and any time you need to update. FG has some sort of personal site and log-on that it asks for but you don't need to update it. It just generally feels like it got lost to time, but never tried to catch up (likely because it would be ""too big"" an opportunity cost).o NPC tokens do not have a border and you need to use an art app to make one so that the whole deal doesn't look garbage. A great deal of FG is trying to make it look good with a system that doesn't give you much help in that department.o Small gripe, but the password system is random and you need to use one of their passwords for some reason. I don't know why this is.Final words: I love playing TTRPGs, but I very much dislike asking people to buy this game and always say to wait for it to be on sale (and even then I feel bad). The biggest problems with this ""game"" are money-oriented. This is because FG is for the money, not the players. Having a pit in my stomach for asking somone to buy this is all that I should need to say."
