76561198008662288,Recommended,252690,28245129,"Posted: 7 December, 2016",all,HeadCase,"An unbelievably awesome program! I have waited years to find something like this. It is a VTT (Virtual Table Top) system for playing any RPG you can imagine. Many of the most popular systems (and their various editions) are either pre-loaded or available for a competitve price. All VTTs have that capability but only Fantasy Grounds has the rulesets LICENSED from publishers like WotC and others. So it is the OFFICIAL stuff and not what some greasy dude half put together and loaded to a forum as on other VTTs.Plus the presentation is epic! Some VTTs have a few bonus gimicks, but once you play FG you will see that the maximum fun and playability is applied with ALL the features you need and more!However, be aware that the learning curve is sharp for the first two hours. You will open it and be WTF do I click, as it isn't setup like someone's VB app dice roller. Watch a few youtube videos and read a bit of the manual. Once you get a few of the icons down, it's fine after that. Any new sections you come to will be easy because you understand the formating and layout of FG. So hard at first, easy forever.And the forum on their website is awesome! So many great people looking to help and looking to run games.100 hour update: Still going strong and the games have been AMAZING! Top tip: watching a couple tutorial videos helped many get over that early learning curve."
