76561198000266166,Not Recommended,252690,21427950,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,Black Hammer,"The software itself is fine; relatively flexible, easy to use if you're already computer literate, and fairly reliable. Aside from a few issues regarding required connectivity for use of aliases or licenses, I have few complaints about the program itself.Unfortunately, I cannot recommend investing in Fantasy Grounds to anyone who doesn't already have a group in mind to play with. The community is largely insular, consisting of groups who already know and play with each other. As either a GM or player, I've seen very little interest or discussion on the official forums and here for most people looking for games.If you're looking for a virtual tabletop for a current group, FG is worth a try. If you're looking to get into a group for an online game, Fantasy Grounds may take some work getting involved with.That being said, many games are run using an Ultimate License, meaning players can often join games and try it out using the demo version of FG. So there is a very solid option for ""try before you buy.""2017 EDIT: Looking at the product currently, I have trouble still recommending it. Like any other multiplayer product, FG must at least partially be judged on the basis of its community. And while I have enjoyed some of my time with it, FG suffers from several issues, mostly related to its userbase:1. If you are not interested in D&D or Pathfinder (and there are hundreds of published RPGs besides that one solitary game line), you will have difficulty getting into a game or getting one started. The community interest simply isn't there for systems outside D&D.2. Unfriendly to outsiders to gaming. I am not new to gaming, and have nearly twenty years of RPGs under my belt. I have mostly gotten along with the FG community fine. Newer people to gaming, whether online gaming or tabletop RPGs in general, have universally told me they had a very negative experience with FG. Whether hostility towards female gamers, unwillingness to work with people with busier lives or schedules, or simply poor etiquette and lack of respect, it seems FG's community has become increasingly polarized in the time I've used it.3. While a major overhaul is in the works, the current version is simply too wooden for my tastes. Many UI elements cannot be adjusted while the game server is launched, the chat window needs more customization options or at least tabs, and adjusting any part of a module, ruleset, or extension requires a significant investment in time and specific tools (free, but still have to be downloaded, updated, and learned)."
